The paper introduces a new class of graph queries called CXRPQs, which are an extension of CRPQs with string variables. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The evaluation complexity of CXRPQs is also discussed, which suggests a possible connection to the complexity theory (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper compares CXRPQs with other query languages, which could relate to the formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper introduces a user-friendly approach to graph queries, which could be relevant to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
